<!-- ==========================================================

Description:
Create Note page template.

This view provides the interface for creating a new note,
including title and content input fields.

Responsibilities:
- Display note creation form.
- Provide save button trigger.
- Support internationalization for labels and placeholders.
- Integrate with client-side note creation logic.

Structure:
- Includes global header and footer partials.
- Organized using BEM methodology.
- Divided into header (title + save action) and form section.

Client-Side Behavior:
- "Save" button triggers note creation logic (handled in crear.js).
- Title and content values are captured via DOM selectors.
- i18n placeholders are dynamically translated.
- Validation and persistence are handled client-side.

Dependencies:
- crear.js
- search.js (for later note indexing if applicable)
- i18n system (data-i18n & data-i18n-placeholder)
- Global bundle.min.js

Notes:
- This template does not perform direct data submission.
- Note persistence is managed through JavaScript modules
  and backend integration (e.g., Firebase).
========================================================== -->

<%- include('partials/header') %>

<main class="crear">

  <header class="crear__header">
    <h1 class="crear__titulo" data-i18n="crear__titulo"></h1>
    <button class="crear__btnSave" id="save-note" data-i18n="crear__btnSave"></button>
  </header>

  <section class="crear__form">
    <input 
      type="text" 
      id="note-title" 
      class="crear__inputTitulo" 
      placeholder="Título de la nota..." 
      data-i18n-placeholder="crear__inputTitulo"
    >

    <textarea 
      id="note-content"
      class="crear__inputContenido"
      placeholder="Escribe tu nota aquí..."
      data-i18n-placeholder="crear__inputContenido"
    ></textarea>
  </section>

</main>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>